					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 13th or 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment. </support>
								<extent rend="visible">323 folios<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>310</height>
										<width>250</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>195/175</height>
										<width>95/165</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>323 folios (+ 1 unfoliated modern flyleaf and 1 unfoliated older paper flyleaf with watermark at the beginning, 1 unfoliated older paper flyleaf and 2 modern unfoliated paper flyleaves with watermark at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>40 quires: i8 (folios 1-8), ii8 (folios 9-16), iii8 (folios 17-24), iv8 (folios 25-32), v8 (folios 33-40), vi8 (folios 41-48), vii12 (folios 49-60), viii8 (folios 61-68), ix8 (folios 69-76), x8 (folios 77-84), xi8 (folios 85-92), xii8 (folios 93-100), xiii8 (folios 101-108), xiv8 (folios 109-116), xv8 (folios 117-124), xvi8 (folios 125-132), xvii8 (folios 133-140), xviii8 (folios 141-148), xix8 (folios 149-156), xx8 (folios 157-164), xxi2 (folios 165-172), xxii10 (folios 173-182), xxiii8 (folios 183-190), xxiv8 (folios 191-198), xxv8 (folios 199-206), xxvi12 (folios 207-218), xxvii8 (folios 219-226), xxviii8 (folios 227-234), xxix8 (folios 235-242), xxx8 (folios 243-250), xxxi8 (folios 251-258), xxxii8 (folios 259-266), xxxiii8 (folios 267-274), xxxiv6 (folios 275-280), xxxv8 (folios 281-288), xxxvi4 (folios 289-292), xxxvii10 (folios 293-302), xxxviii5 (folios 303-307), xxxix8 (folios 308-315), xl8 (folios 316-323).</p>
									<p>Quires marked with catchwords.</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="24 26" writtenLines="23 25">
									<p>Pricking and ruling are visible. </p>
									<p>Watermark on iii recto, of a fleur de lys, similar to <ref target="Briquet_1968" type="number">7126</ref>  (dated <date calendar="Gregorian">1582</date>, <name type="place">Vicenza</name>). </p>
									<p>Watermark, [324r], of a horn included into a crowned shield and with the letters LVG, similar to <ref target="Heawood_1950" type="number">2745</ref> (dated 1755, London).</p>
									<p>Closely cut margins.</p>
									<p>A large number of smaller and greater omissions from text, Targum and commentary have been subsequently supplied in the margins by various hands.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Ashkenazi square and semi-cursive script, partially punctuated.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major">
								<p>
									<locus n="1r, 1v, 8r, 8v"/> and <locus from="308r" to="323v"/>: due to a different hand.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="scribe">Ḥayim Kohen</name>: probably of folios 1-307: the word Kohen is marked many times, e.g., 95r, 104r, 116v, 128v, 262r; the word Ḥayim is decorated on 204r. </p>
							<p>Probably censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Hippolite of Ferrara</name>, Franciscan: inscribed 'Fra Hipp. Ferr' (active at the end of the 16th century-beginning of 17th century, in Cremona) (folio 323v), see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">18-19, 93</ref>.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="bookseller">Nataniel Noel</name> (fl. 1681, d. 1753), employed by <name type="person" role="owner">Edward Harley</name> for buying books and manuscripts chiefly on the Continent, where his agent was <name type="person" role="bookseller">George Suttie</name> (<ref target="Wright_1972"/>): sold to Edward Harley on <date calendar="Gregorian">18 January 1723/4</date>; date inscribed ([ii recto]).</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p> 	Post-1600. Black leather with the Harley coat of arms in the centre.</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
					</physDesc>
